author: COMSOL
description: In nuclear fusion reactors, liquid metal will interact with the background magnetic field in a flow regime known as magnetohydrodynamics (MHD). This model demonstrates MHD flow in the duct of a liquid metal blanket, where the electromagnetic field and the fluid flow are coupled via the Lorentz force and electromotive force, and the fluid flow is coupled with heat transfer.
